issue.body:
Hello Yii2 community, 
I have an unexpected situation going on.

Our setup is distributed system
php 7.1.2 (2 servers)
mysql 5.7 (1 server)
yii 2.0.9

the following code is generating an unexpected error

```
$transactions = new Transactions();
$transactions->attributes = $input['basic'];
$transactions->voucher_id = $voucher->id;

if (!$transactions->save()) {
    logErrorsInFile('transaction', $transactions);
    throw new \yii\db\Exception('Error in adding transactions');
} else {
     // Payers Transaction
     foreach ($input['payers'] as $payer) {
         $transactionDetail = new TransactionDetails();
         $transactionDetail->transaction_id = $transactions->id;
         $transactionDetail->attributes = $payer;

         if (!$transactionDetail->save()) {
             logErrorsInFile('transaction_details', $transactionDetail);
             throw new \yii\db\Exception('Error in transactions_details payer');
        }
    }
}
```
In the above code the $transactionDetail->save() is generating error say **1/50 times**.
generated error logged is 
```
print_r($transactionDetail->errors);
Array
(
    [transaction_id] => Array
        (
            [0] => Transaction ID is invalid.
        )

)

```
where *transaction_id* is a field in *transaction_details* table and refers to primary key **id** of **transactions** table

Observation:
a record is properly inserted in **transactions** table and the **id** that is referenced in **transaction_details** table is valid

I am unable to understand why the model->errors is giving **is invalid ** error.
this is not happening every time. it is happening very randomly and ratio is almost 1/50

since this is a critical part in our application, i want to figure out the main cause of this error. 
any help or pointers would be appreciated.

thanks in advance.
